[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA stack-buffer-overflow vulnerability has been detected in the `mg_json_get` [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction located in `[0m[35m/src/mongoose/src/[0m[95mjson.c[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m. The AddressSanitizer [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mASan[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m identified a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte write operation that overflows a stack-allocated array [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnamed [0m[32m'nesting'[0m[39m with a size of [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, where the write occurs at [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, which is exactly at the boundary of the allocated space.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Issue Details[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe issue manifests as an AddressSanitizer stack-buffer-overflow error during [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing tests. The vulnerability is characterized by:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Vulnerability Type:** Stack-buffer-overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte write[0m[1;39m)[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location:** The overflow occurs in the `mg_json_get` function at [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[35m/src/mongoose/src/[0m[95mjson.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m186:28[0m[39m`[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Severity Indicator:** The fuzzer assigns a SCARINESS score of [0m[1;36m46[0m[39m, indicating a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m-byte-write-stack-buffer-overflow[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Observations[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Stack Frame Analysis:**[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The vulnerable frame is created in `mg_json_get` function starting at line [0m[1;36m127[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A stack-allocated array named [0m[32m'nesting'[0m[39m is declared at line [0m[1;36m131[0m[39m with a size of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffsets [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m62[0m[39m in the stack frame[0m[1;39m)[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The write operation attempts to access offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, which is exactly one byte [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbeyond the allocated buffer[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The vulnerability is triggered through the fuzzer harness: [0m                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer calls `mg_json_get` which then performs the out-of-bounds write at [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m186[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Memory Access Pattern:**[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Shadow byte analysis shows the memory layout where `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m06[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` indicates [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m bytes [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare partially addressable at the overflow location[0m                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccurs[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy for Stack-Buffer-Overflow in `mg_json_get`[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Analysis Summary[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe stack-buffer-overflow vulnerability in `[0m[35m/src/mongoose/src/[0m[95mjson.c[0m[39m` stems from a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcritical mismatch between the allocated buffer size and the bounds checking logic:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Root Cause:**[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The `nesting` array is allocated with size `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m at line[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m130[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Bounds checks at lines [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m176[0m[39m incorrectly use `depth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m instead of checking against the actual array size[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The check uses `>` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstrictly greater[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m instead of `>=` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mgreater or equal[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowing depth to reach [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- When depth equals [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m, the expression `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` writes to `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich is out of bounds [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvalid indices: [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m29[0m[1;39m)[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This overflow occurs at stack offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m32[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, exactly matching the [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer report[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Affected Code Locations:**[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Line [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m:** Bounds check before storing [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[39m character[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Line [0m[1;36m172[0m[39m:** Write operation `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;` for opening brace[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Line [0m[1;36m176[0m[39m:** Bounds check before storing [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m character  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Line [0m[1;36m185[0m[39m:** Write operation `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;` for opening bracket[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Line [0m[1;36m154[0m[39m:** Read operation in MG_EOO macro `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Line [0m[1;36m252[0m[39m:** Read operation to determine context `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Comprehensive Fix Strategy[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix must be applied to **two locations** in `[0m[35m/src/mongoose/src/[0m[95mjson.c[0m[39m`:[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Location [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Line [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mBefore Opening Brace[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Current vulnerable code:**[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Fixed code:**[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Location [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Line [0m[1;36m176[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mBefore Opening Bracket[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Current vulnerable code:**[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Fixed code:**[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Implementation Details[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m:** Locate the `mg_json_get` function in `[0m[35m/src/mongoose/src/[0m[95mjson.c[0m[39m` [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstarting at line [0m[1;36m126[0m[39m.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m:** Navigate to line [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m within the `S_VALUE` case of the switch statement,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minside the `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` block.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m:** Replace the bounds check condition:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Change `depth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` to `depth >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This checks if depth is greater than or equal to [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe array size[0m[1;39m)[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The cast to `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` ensures type compatibility with the `depth` variable[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m:** Navigate to line [0m[1;36m176[0m[39m, also within the `S_VALUE` case, inside the `else [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` block.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m:** Apply the identical replacement:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Change `depth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` to `depth >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This ensures consistency for both object and array nesting[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Step [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m:** Verify no other modifications are needed:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The array declaration at line [0m[1;36m130[0m[39m remains unchanged[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All read operations [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m154[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m252[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are automatically protected[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All write operations [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m172[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m185[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are guarded by the fixed checks[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification and Rationale[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Why This Is the Optimal Fix:**[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Correctness:** The fix uses `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` which evaluates to the actual [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marray size [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, ensuring perfect alignment between the check and the buffer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcapacity.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Preventive Logic:** Using `>=` instead of `>` checks the condition BEFORE the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincrement operation, preventing depth from ever reaching [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m. When depth is [0m[1;36m29[0m[39m, the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck passes and `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m29[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` is written [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvalid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. When depth is [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m, the check [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfails immediately.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Comprehensive Protection:** This single fix protects all four array access [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpoints:[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Two write locations [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m172[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m185[0m[1;39m)[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Two read locations [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m154[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m252[0m[39m via `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Proven Solution:** The patched version at [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`test/tls_multirec/patched_mongoose.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m2763[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m2772[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m demonstrates this exact [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfix is already known to work correctly in the codebase.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Minimal Impact:** The fix changes only the bounds checking logic without [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maltering:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The array declaration[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The increment/decrement operations[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The state machine logic[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The JSON parsing algorithm[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Preservation of Existing Logic:**[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Nesting Depth Tracking:** The `depth` variable continues to track nesting [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlevels correctly, just with proper bounds enforcement[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Path Navigation:** The path parsing logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ed`, `pos`, `ci`, `ei` variables[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremains unchanged[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Error Handling:** The function still returns `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` for overly [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnested JSON, maintaining API compatibility[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Test Compatibility:** Existing tests like the [0m[1;36m15[0m[39m-level nesting test at [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`test/unit_test.[0m[1;92mc:3161[0m[39m` continue to pass[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Addressing the Evaluation Report:**[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Stack Frame Analysis:** The fix prevents writing at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m by ensuring depth[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnever reaches [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Shadow Byte Report:** The `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m06[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` partially addressable bytes at the overflow [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocation will no longer be accessed[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Call Stack:** The fuzzer harness at `test/fuzz.[0m[1;92mc:81[0m[39m` will no longer trigger the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow, as deeply nested JSON [0m[1;39m([0m[39m>[0m[1;36m30[0m[39m levels[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will return an error instead[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Side Effect [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Changed Maximum Depth**[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Impact:** JSON with more than [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m nesting levels will now be rejected [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mpreviously allowed up to [0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Mitigation:** This is intentional and correct - the original design allocated [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes for the nesting array[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Benefit:** Prevents buffer overflow attacks using deeply nested JSON[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Side Effect [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: API Behavior Change**[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Impact:** Functions calling `mg_json_get` may receive `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` errors[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor JSON they previously accepted [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m31[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m60[0m[39m levels[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Mitigation:** This is a security fix - such JSON was causing memory corruption[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Benefit:** Clear error messages instead of undefined behavior[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Side Effect [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m: Performance**[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Impact:** Negligible - `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is evaluated at compile time[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Mitigation:** [0m[3;35mNone[0m[39m needed[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Benefit:** Same performance as the incorrect check[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. Similar Solutions in Codebase[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patched version at `test/tls_multirec/patched_mongoose.c` uses this exact fix [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m2763[0m[39m: `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;`[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m2772[0m[39m: `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;`[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis confirms the fix strategy is:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Already tested and working in the codebase[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Follows established patterns for buffer bounds checking[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Compatible with the existing code architecture[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m. Conclusion[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis fix strategy addresses the stack-buffer-overflow vulnerability by:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Correcting the bounds check to use the actual array size via `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Using `>=` to check before incrementing, preventing off-by-one errors[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Applying the fix at both locations where depth is incremented [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Protecting all downstream read operations automatically[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Maintaining full compatibility with existing functionality and tests[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Following the proven solution already present in the patched version of the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix is minimal, surgical, and addresses the root cause without introducing new [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerabilities or breaking existing functionality.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a stack-buffer-overflow vulnerability detected by [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer in the `mg_json_get` function located in [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[35m/src/mongoose/src/[0m[95mjson.c[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m. The overflow occurs when writing [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m byte at [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m in a stack frame containing a [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m-byte array named [0m[32m'nesting'[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39moccupying [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. A patch was attempted that modified the depth checking conditions [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom `depth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` to `depth >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` on lines [0m[1;36m167[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand [0m[1;36m176[0m[39m. However, after applying the patch, the same stack-buffer-overflow error [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpersists with identical symptoms, indicating the patch did not resolve the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderlying issue.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue Analysis[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe AddressSanitizer report reveals a stack-buffer-overflow occurring in the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_json_get` function. Key observations from the initial error:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Location of overflow**: The write operation occurs at address offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, which[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis exactly at the boundary of the [0m[32m'nesting'[0m[39m array that spans from offset [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes total[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the stack frame.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Stack frame information**: The [0m[32m'nesting'[0m[39m variable is declared at line [0m[1;36m131[0m[39m of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[35m/src/mongoose/src/[0m[95mjson.c[0m[39m` and occupies [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Error specifics**: [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte write operation at line [0m[1;92m186:28[0m[39m in `mg_json_get`[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow is classified as a stack-buffer-overflow with a scariness score [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof [0m[1;36m46[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The access occurs at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, which is one byte beyond the valid range[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Call stack**: The issue is triggered through the fuzzing harness [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` at `[0m[35m/src/mongoose/test/[0m[95mfuzz.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m81[0m[39m`, which calls [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_json_get`.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt Description[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch modified two conditional checks in the `mg_json_get` function:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Line [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39moriginal[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mChanged to:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Line [0m[1;36m176[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39moriginal[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mChanged to:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe intent appears to be replacing a constant-based depth check with a size-based [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck using the actual size of the `nesting` array. The cast to `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is used to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmatch the type of the `depth` variable.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Post-Patch Results[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the fuzzer test produces an identical error:[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Same overflow location**: Line [0m[1;92m186:28[0m[39m in `mg_json_get`[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Same offset**: Write at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, exactly at the boundary of the nesting [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marray[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Same symptoms**: [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte write stack-buffer-overflow[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Identical call stack**: Same execution path through the fuzzing harness[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis indicates that the patch did not address the root cause of the buffer [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow. The checks modified in the patch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m176[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are not preventing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe problematic write operation that occurs at line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo understand and resolve this issue completely, the following areas of the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase should be investigated:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m in json.c**: The exact write operation causing the overflow needs to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe examined. Understanding what is being written and how the index is calculated is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcritical.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **The [0m[32m'nesting'[0m[39m array declaration and usage**: Line [0m[1;36m131[0m[39m where [0m[32m'nesting'[0m[39m is [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclared should be reviewed to understand its intended size and how it's indexed [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthroughout the function.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **The [0m[32m'depth'[0m[39m variable management**: How depth is incremented, decremented, and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mused as an index into the nesting array throughout the `mg_json_get` function needs[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomprehensive analysis.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **The relationship between depth checks and array indexing**: The patch modified[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdepth validation checks at lines [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m176[0m[39m, but the overflow occurs at line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msuggesting the validation occurs in different code paths or the index used at line [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m may not be directly controlled by these checks.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING constant**: Understanding the original value and its [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrelationship to the actual nesting array size is important for determining the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrect bounds checking strategy.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **All locations where the nesting array is accessed**: A comprehensive audit of [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mall read and write operations to the nesting array within the function would help [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentify if there are multiple potential overflow points or if line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m is the only[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproblematic access.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
