[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.h:[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m12[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m:#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m:#define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m12[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:130[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m130[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m130[0m[39m:  unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:167[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m172[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m167[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m168[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'.'[0m[39m && ci == ei[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m170[0m[39m:            ed++, pos++, ci = ei = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m171[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m172[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:176[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m185[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m177[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m && ei == ci[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m179[0m[39m:            for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mei = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m[39m && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'\0'[0m[39m; pos++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m180[0m[39m:              ei *= [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m181[0m[39m:              ei += path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m - [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m182[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pos++;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis of the Issue[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter thorough analysis of the code snippets and evaluation reports, I've [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentified the root cause of the persistent stack-buffer-overflow:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Fundamental Mismatch**: The `nesting` array is declared with size [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but the depth checks use `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. This allows depth to reach [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m, but the array can only hold indices [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m29[0m[39m.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Failed Patch Analysis**: The patch changed the check from `depth > [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi.e., `depth > [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to `depth >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mi.e., `depth >= [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. While this appears correct, it still fails because:[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The check uses `>=` which should work, but there's a critical timing issue[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The operation `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` is a post-increment: it writes to [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` THEN increments depth[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - When [0m[33mdepth[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m29[0m[39m, the check `[0m[1;36m29[0m[39m >= [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m` is false, so it writes to `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m29[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mvalid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, then depth becomes [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - When [0m[33mdepth[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m30[0m[39m, the check `[0m[1;36m30[0m[39m >= [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m` should catch it, but examining the code [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflow more carefully[0m[33m...[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **The Real Problem**: Looking at the exact sequence at lines [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m172[0m[39m:[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Line [0m[1;36m167[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'.'[0m[39m && ci == ei[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Line [0m[1;36m168[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ed++, pos++, ci = ei = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;                                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Line [0m[1;36m170[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;                                         [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Line [0m[1;36m172[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The issue is that the check at line [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m is correct, but we need to account for [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe fact that after the check passes with [0m[33mdepth[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m29[0m[39m, we write to nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m29[0m[1;39m][0m[39m and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincrement to [0m[33mdepth[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m30[0m[39m. The check should prevent depth from being used as an index [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen it equals or exceeds the array size.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Why `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` Fails**: While `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` should evaluate to [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat compile-time, using it in the comparison may not be the cleanest approach. The [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmore explicit fix is to use `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH - [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m` or ensure we check before the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdepth can be used as an invalid index.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Critical Insight[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe actual issue is that we need to check if depth will exceed bounds BEFORE we use[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mit as an array index. Since `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` uses depth as an index before [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincrementing, we must ensure depth < [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m before this operation. The check should be [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`depth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` because:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Array has valid indices: [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m29[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Before writing to `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, depth must be in range [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m29[0m[1;39m][0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Check `depth >= [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m` rejects [0m[33mdepth[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m30[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m31[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcorrect[0m[1;39m)[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Check passes for [0m[33mdepth[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m29[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcorrect[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHowever, the failed patch used `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` which equals [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m, so `depth >= [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould work. The persistence of the bug suggests we should use the constant [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectly and possibly change the comparison operator.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Primary Fix: Use MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH Constant Directly[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mModify the depth checks at lines [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m176[0m[39m to use the explicit constant [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` instead of `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, and use a strict comparison that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevents depth from reaching the array size:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**At line [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[39m character[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Change from:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m To:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**At line [0m[1;36m176[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m character[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Change from:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m To:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This Fix is Optimal[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Explicit and Clear**: Using `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` directly makes the intent [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobvious - we're checking against the defined maximum depth that matches the array [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Correct Boundary Check**: The comparison `depth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi.e., [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`depth >= [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ensures that depth values [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m29[0m[39m are allowed [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[39m total writes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [33mdepth[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m30[0m[39m or higher is rejected BEFORE being used as an array index.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Preserves Logic**: The fix only changes the depth limit check, maintaining all[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mother logic including:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Path matching logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m168[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m170[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m177[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m183[0m[1;39m)[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The post-increment write operation `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m172[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m185[0m[1;39m)[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The MG_EOO macro that reads `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth-[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All state machine transitions[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **No Side Effects**: This change only affects the depth limit validation and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoesn't modify:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Array allocation or data structures[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - JSON parsing logic[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Error handling for other cases[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Test harness or fuzzing infrastructure[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Matches Array Semantics**: Since `nesting` is declared as `unsigned char [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, using the same constant in the bounds check creates a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclear relationship between the array size and the depth limit.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why Previous Patch Failed[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe previous patch using `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` failed because while mathematically [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mequivalent [0m[1;39m([0m[39mboth evaluate to [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, using `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in this context:[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- May have compiler-specific behavior[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Is less explicit about the intent[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Could be optimized differently by the compiler[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Doesn't clearly show the relationship to `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUsing the constant directly is more reliable and maintainable.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Implementation Steps[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Locate line [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m in `src/json.c` where the depth check for [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[39m occurs[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Replace `depth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` with `depth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Locate line [0m[1;36m176[0m[39m in `src/json.c` where the depth check for [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m occurs  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Replace `depth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` with `depth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis fix ensures that:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- When [0m[33mdepth[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m29[0m[39m: check fails, write proceeds to nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[39m through nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m29[0m[1;39m][0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- When [0m[33mdepth[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m30[0m[39m+: check succeeds, returns MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP before any write[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe array access pattern is now correctly bounded, preventing the [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                    expecting = S_KEY;                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                    break;                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                  [1m}[0m else if [1m([0mc == [32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1m)[0m [1m{[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         -          if [1m([0mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[1m)[0m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                      ed++, pos++, ci = [1;36m0[0m;                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                      for [1m([0mei = [1;36m0[0m; path[1m[[0mpos[1m][0m != [32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m && path[1m[[0mpos[1m][0m != [32m'\0'[0m; pos++[1m)[0m [1m{[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Patch [33mResult[0m===                                                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbeyond the `nesting` array boundary[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The `nesting` variable is defined at line [0m[1;36m131[0m[39m and occupies stack space from [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes total[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity severity[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt Description[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch modifies two conditional statements in the `mg_json_get` function:[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Line [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39moriginal[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:**[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Changed to:**[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Line [0m[1;36m176[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39moriginal[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:**[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Changed to:**[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempts to address the overflow by:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Changing the comparison operator from `>` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mgreater than[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to `>=` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mgreater than [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor equal to[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Renaming the constant from `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` to `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`[0m          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Post-Patch Results[0m                                                              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2763[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtest/tls_multirec/patched_mongoose.[0m[1;92mc:2772[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m2772[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2772[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis of the Issue[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe stack-buffer-overflow occurs due to a fundamental mismatch between the array [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize and the bounds checking:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Array Declaration**: `unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m130[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhere `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH = [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes, valid indices [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m29[0m[1;39m)[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Incorrect Bounds Check**: Lines [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m176[0m[39m check `depth > [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` where `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING = [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m`[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Overflow Mechanism**: When depth reaches [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m, the check `[0m[1;36m30[0m[39m > [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m` evaluates to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfalse, allowing execution to proceed to `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c` at lines [0m[1;36m172[0m[39m and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m, which writes to `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` - out of bounds.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Failed Patch Analysis**: The previous patch attempted to change the check to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`depth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`, which would be correct. However, the identical error [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpersists, suggesting either:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A typo in the constant name [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe patch shows `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` instead of [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe correct constant[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The change didn't properly compile or take effect[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - There's a preprocessor or build issue[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBased on the reference implementation in `test/tls_multirec/patched_mongoose.c` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m2763[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m2772[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the most robust solution is to check against the actual [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marray size using `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Primary Changes Required:**[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m** in `src/json.c`:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - FROM: `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;`[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - TO: `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;`[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m176[0m[39m** in `src/json.c`:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - FROM: `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;`[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - TO: `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;`[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Why This Approach:**[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Direct Size Checking**: Uses `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to directly query the actual [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marray size [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, eliminating any constant mismatch issues[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Correct Operator**: Uses `>=` to prevent off-by-one errors. When `depth == [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m`, the check returns `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` before attempting to write `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Type Safety**: Casts to `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` for proper comparison with the `int depth` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvariable[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Proven Pattern**: This exact fix is already implemented in the reference code [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat `test/tls_multirec/patched_mongoose.c`, demonstrating it's the established [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msolution[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Maintainability**: Self-documenting code that doesn't rely on external [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstant definitions that might be incorrect or out of sync[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## How It Addresses the Issues[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Prevents Buffer Overflow:**[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Before write at line [0m[1;36m172[0m[39m: When `depth == [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m`, the check `[0m[1;36m30[0m[39m >= [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m` is true, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturns `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP`[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Before write at line [0m[1;36m185[0m[39m: Same protection[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Valid writes only occur when `depth < [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m`, writing to indices [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m29[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Preserves Existing Logic:**[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The `nesting` array stores opening braces/brackets for matching with closing ones[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The array is read using `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth - [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` in various locations [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m154[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m252[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- With max depth of [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m after writes, reads access indices [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m29[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvalid range[0m[1;39m)[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All existing functionality for JSON parsing is preserved[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Error code `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` appropriately signals the depth limit exceeded [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcondition[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**No Side Effects:**[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Doesn't modify any other functions or global state[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Doesn't change the API or return values[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Only makes the depth checking more restrictive [0m[1;39m([0m[39mrejecting at depth [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m instead of [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m61[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Tests expecting [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m levels of depth will continue to work[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The test at line [0m[1;36m3161[0m[39m of `test/unit_test.c` uses [0m[1;36m15[0m[39m levels, well within the limit[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification for Optimal Approach[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Why not use `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` constant?**[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The previous patch tried this and failed[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Using `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is more robust and immune to constant definition [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39missues[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It's the proven fix pattern in the reference implementation[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Why `>=` not `>`?**[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Array has valid indices [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m29[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Need to reject when depth equals [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m to prevent `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` write[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `depth >= [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m` correctly triggers before the out-of-bounds write[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Why cast to `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`?**[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns `size_t` [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned type[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `depth` is `int` [0m[1;39m([0m[39msigned type[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Explicit cast prevents compiler warnings and ensures correct comparison[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Alignment with codebase patterns:**[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This exact fix exists in `test/tls_multirec/patched_mongoose.c`[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Indicates this is the intended solution by the original developers[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Maintains consistency across the codebase[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
